feat: 0.3.0-beta.5 — per-developer cost attribution (P2)

Second slice of the enterprise cost wedge. mint cost-report now
answers "who spent what on AI this month?" — the first enterprise
client's #1 ask.

- resolveDeveloper(): MINT_DEVELOPER -> git config user.email
  -> os.userInfo().username -> 'unknown'. Cached per-process.
- usage.db: new `developer` column via idempotent ALTER TABLE +
  idx_usage_developer_ts index. Existing installs upgrade safely.
- mint cost-report --by developer|model|day for grouped views.
- mint cost-report --developer <id> filters to one dev.
- CSV/JSON exports include the developer column on both the
  per-session and grouped paths.

Tests: 4 new in src/usage/__tests__/developer-attribution.test.ts.
Total 77/77 pass (+8 since beta.3). Build 466 KB.
